1
00:00:22,656 --> 00:00:25,191
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Whoa, hold on a minute! Who's</i>
<i>that girl with Mamo?</i>

2
00:00:25,358 --> 00:00:27,460
<i>(Chibi‐Usa)</i>
<i>She say she's your love rival!</i>

3
00:00:27,528 --> 00:00:30,597
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>My what ?! Does she think</i>
<i>she can steal Mamo from me?</i>

4
00:00:30,864 --> 00:00:33,199
<i>Well, that's just useless,</i>
<i>useless, useless, useless!...</i>

5
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:36,703
<i>Hey, she's attacking him! No one</i>
<i>gets away with that!</i>

6
00:00:37,370 --> 00:00:40,707
In the name of the Moon...
We'll punish you!

7
00:00:44,611 --> 00:00:54,655
♪

8
00:00:54,655 --> 00:01:14,681
♪

9
00:01:14,681 --> 00:01:34,701
♪

10
00:01:34,701 --> 00:01:54,721
♪

11
00:01:54,721 --> 00:02:12,613
♪

12
00:02:20,220 --> 00:02:22,956
<i>Usagi</i>)
<i>Shadow of Evil: The</i>
<i>Trio's Last Chance</i>

13
00:02:28,595 --> 00:02:33,099
<i>(Tiger's Eye)</i>
<i>Humph! Another scolding...</i>

14
00:02:33,099 --> 00:02:35,468
Doesn't the old witch realize
we're doing our best?&

15
00:02:35,502 --> 00:02:41,575
It's true. She should at least
give us a chance to explain
before yelling at us.

16
00:02:41,608 --> 00:02:47,581
<i>Exactly! We have no idea whose</i>
<i>dreams Pegasus is hiding in, so</i>
<i>obviously, it's going to take</i>

17
00:02:47,614 --> 00:02:49,750
<i>time... But does she sympathize?</i>

18
00:02:49,783 --> 00:02:52,085
No, all we get from her is...

19
00:02:52,118 --> 00:02:54,655
“You worthless incompetents
have failed again ”"

20
00:02:54,688 --> 00:02:59,593
“Good grief, when are you
finally going to capture
Pegasus, you good‐for‐nothing
numbskulls ”"

21
00:02:59,626 --> 00:03:01,301
Right?

22
00:03:01,301 --> 00:03:02,836
Not bad.

23
00:03:02,869 --> 00:03:04,304
<i>(Hawk's Eye)</i>
<i>Thanks, I've been</i>
<i>working on it for a while.</i>

24
00:03:04,505 --> 00:03:07,140
<i>(Tiger's Eye)</i>
<i>Oh, so you've got time for that</i>
<i>but not for any real work!</i>

25
00:03:07,173 --> 00:03:08,809
<i>(Hawk's Eye)</i>
<i>That's a whole</i>
<i>different thing.</i>

26
00:03:08,809 --> 00:03:09,643
Whatta you mean, a whole
different thing?! If you've got
time for one, you've got‐‐

27
00:03:09,643 --> 00:03:12,012
<i>(Fish's Eye)</i>
<i>Cut it out, guys&</i>

28
00:03:12,045 --> 00:03:12,979
‐Hm?
‐Hm?

29
00:03:13,013 --> 00:03:14,648
What's wrong, Fish's Eye?

30
00:03:14,648 --> 00:03:16,517
Yeah, why so melancholy?

31
00:03:16,550 --> 00:03:19,119
I'm not. It's just,

32
00:03:19,152 --> 00:03:23,156
what do you think is going to
happen to the three of us if we
keep failing to find Pegasus?

33
00:03:23,156 --> 00:03:25,158
Search me.

34
00:03:25,158 --> 00:03:26,326
I don't know.

35
00:03:26,326 --> 00:03:28,294
Probably nothing that bad.

36
00:03:28,328 --> 00:03:31,732
It's almost like the Madame
doesn't expect us to succeed.

37
00:03:31,798 --> 00:03:34,535
Well, you do
have a point there.

38
00:03:34,568 --> 00:03:36,002
Huh?
<i>[wings flapping]</i>

39
00:03:36,036 --> 00:03:38,004
Oh, it's Zircon.

40
00:03:40,674 --> 00:03:43,476
Our new target, huh?

41
00:03:43,510 --> 00:03:45,045
<i>(Tiger's Eye)</i>
<i>You want to handle this one?...</i>

42
00:03:45,078 --> 00:03:48,181
‐Huh!? It's a guy!?
‐Huh!? It's a guy!?

43
00:03:48,214 --> 00:03:50,316
[big swoon]

44
00:03:50,350 --> 00:03:53,019
He's...gorgeous!!

45
00:03:54,588 --> 00:03:58,324
Hey! What happened?
Weren't you all melancholy
just a minute ago?!

46
00:03:58,358 --> 00:04:00,661
This is a whole different thing.

47
00:04:00,694 --> 00:04:04,204
You really do love the guys,
don't you, Fish's Eye?

48
00:04:04,204 --> 00:04:08,174
Yeah, that may be, but he
still gets dumped a lot.

49
00:04:08,208 --> 00:04:10,511
Only because I
wasn't even trying!

50
00:04:10,544 --> 00:04:13,346
Once I get serious, there's
no person alive I can't win!

51
00:04:13,379 --> 00:04:14,781
Pretty big talk.

52
00:04:14,848 --> 00:04:16,783
Then let's see you get
serious for a change.

53
00:04:16,850 --> 00:04:19,853
Huh! I will, but they gotta
be worth the effort.

54
00:04:19,886 --> 00:04:24,224
[sigh] And this one's definitely
worth the effort.

55
00:04:25,425 --> 00:04:29,730
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Soo cute! Oh my</i>
<i>gosh..! [giggle]</i>

56
00:04:29,730 --> 00:04:33,233
Oooh! And that one!
And that one...

57
00:04:33,266 --> 00:04:35,401
<i>Haaa what a goofy face!</i>

58
00:04:35,401 --> 00:04:37,203
But still cute!

59
00:04:37,236 --> 00:04:40,240
Look at this one over
here! He's cute, too!

60
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:42,576
Oh, and this one
is cuter! Ha ha ha!

61
00:04:42,576 --> 00:04:44,210
No! This one's cuter! Hee hee!

62
00:04:44,244 --> 00:04:45,746
Wow...

63
00:04:45,812 --> 00:04:49,550
Those fish are very rare.
They're from the Amazon River
in South America.

64
00:04:49,583 --> 00:04:51,752
They're like little
swimming jewels.

65
00:04:51,752 --> 00:04:53,119
They are pretty.

66
00:04:53,153 --> 00:04:55,556
Yeah. I'm tempted to
get some myself.

67
00:04:58,258 --> 00:05:00,466
Oh, boy... they sure
do look tasty.

68
00:05:00,501 --> 00:05:02,569
[groans]

69
00:05:02,603 --> 00:05:05,772
Have you always been into
tropical fish, Mamoru?

70
00:05:05,772 --> 00:05:07,473
Uh‐huh.

71
00:05:07,508 --> 00:05:11,645
I thought it was time I tried
introducing some more exotic
species into my collection.

72
00:05:11,678 --> 00:05:14,915
But don't you think the tank
in your room is already too
crowded?

73
00:05:14,948 --> 00:05:20,153
Hmm... You seem to know a lot
about what's going on in his
room, Usagi.

74
00:05:20,186 --> 00:05:22,823
[embarrassed sigh]

75
00:05:22,856 --> 00:05:25,792
Ahh! What a coupla' love birds!

76
00:05:25,826 --> 00:05:28,294
Hey, that's enough, cut it out!
Stop it, you're embarrassing
me!...

77
00:05:28,328 --> 00:05:31,297
<i>(Minako)</i>
<i>Oh, come on, Usagi!</i>

78
00:05:31,331 --> 00:05:33,466
<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>Bingo. There he is.</i>

79
00:05:37,838 --> 00:05:39,706
[small grunt]

80
00:05:43,877 --> 00:05:47,881
Why do you keep fish as pets?
They're so boring.

81
00:05:47,948 --> 00:05:49,516
Huh?

82
00:05:49,583 --> 00:05:53,687
Is it because they fill a
yearning left in your heart by
your current girlfriend?

83
00:05:58,291 --> 00:05:59,492
Who're you?

84
00:05:59,526 --> 00:06:01,902
[giggle]

85
00:06:01,968 --> 00:06:07,674
I feel so sorry for
your pet fish.

86
00:06:07,674 --> 00:06:09,342
[gasp]

87
00:06:09,342 --> 00:06:13,246
It's lonely being in a
relationship with a glass wall
between you. [pained gasp]

88
00:06:13,313 --> 00:06:14,815
[gasp]

89
00:06:14,848 --> 00:06:15,882
Are you okay!?

90
00:06:15,916 --> 00:06:17,250
Ow...

91
00:06:17,317 --> 00:06:18,852
(Mamoru)
Looks like you've cut yourself.

92
00:06:18,852 --> 00:06:21,187
[gasp]

93
00:06:23,757 --> 00:06:27,360
[shy sigh]

94
00:06:36,837 --> 00:06:39,405
Can I see your hand?

95
00:06:39,439 --> 00:06:41,207
Oh! Yeah.

96
00:06:45,411 --> 00:06:46,680
[gasp]

97
00:06:47,581 --> 00:06:48,949
[gasp]

98
00:06:49,516 --> 00:06:51,885
<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>What was it that I just felt?...</i>

99
00:06:51,918 --> 00:06:55,221
<i>Could he be..?</i>

100
00:06:55,255 --> 00:06:59,359
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Ohh, Mamooo???</i>

101
00:06:59,392 --> 00:07:00,594
Usako?

102
00:07:00,627 --> 00:07:02,402
What were you just doing?

103
00:07:02,402 --> 00:07:04,437
Wait! Wait, it's not
what you think!

104
00:07:04,470 --> 00:07:07,373
No makeup, zero sex appeal...

105
00:07:07,407 --> 00:07:10,977
figure isn't bad, I guess, but
still, it's pretty obvious who
wins this contest.

106
00:07:11,044 --> 00:07:12,478
What!?

107
00:07:12,546 --> 00:07:14,581
Sorry, but I'm
taking him from you.

108
00:07:14,615 --> 00:07:15,882
Hey, hey, hey‐‐

109
00:07:15,916 --> 00:07:19,285
What did you just say??!...
Hyaah!

110
00:07:20,286 --> 00:07:22,923
Who are you, anyway?!

111
00:07:22,923 --> 00:07:25,592
Well, let's just say I'm
your love rival, okay?

112
00:07:25,626 --> 00:07:27,060
My rival?!!

113
00:07:27,093 --> 00:07:31,632
Yep. Even though, frankly,
my dear, you're not really
much of a rival.

114
00:07:31,665 --> 00:07:33,934
[low groaning]

115
00:07:33,967 --> 00:07:35,802
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Mamo, what's going on here?!</i>

116
00:07:35,836 --> 00:07:36,737
<i>(Mamoru)</i>
<i>I‐‐I don't know!</i>

117
00:07:36,770 --> 00:07:37,838
What's the matter?

118
00:07:37,904 --> 00:07:39,773
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>I demand an explanation!</i>

119
00:07:39,773 --> 00:07:42,609
<i>(Mamoru)</i>
<i>Don't look at me! I'm just</i>
<i>as confused as you are!</i>

120
00:07:42,643 --> 00:07:45,679
[sniff sniff] I
know that smell...

121
00:07:45,746 --> 00:07:46,913
A cat!!?

122
00:07:46,947 --> 00:07:49,750
Calm down, Usako, are
you barking at me!?
[barking]

123
00:07:50,350 --> 00:07:52,452
Wait...

124
00:07:52,452 --> 00:07:56,322
Sorry, something just came up so
I really have to get going, but
I'll see you again soon, okay?
Bye‐bye now!

125
00:07:56,356 --> 00:07:59,459
Who was that?

126
00:07:59,459 --> 00:08:00,801
No idea...

127
00:08:03,670 --> 00:08:04,971
[panting]

128
00:08:04,971 --> 00:08:07,107
<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>I was so close...</i>

129
00:08:07,140 --> 00:08:08,675
[gasp]

130
00:08:09,810 --> 00:08:12,445
<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>I sensed a powerful energy...</i>

131
00:08:12,478 --> 00:08:15,816
<i>He definitely could</i>
<i>be Pegasus's host...</i>

132
00:08:15,816 --> 00:08:19,620
<i>And he's really</i>
<i>handsome, too...!</i>

133
00:08:19,653 --> 00:08:25,025
<i>I could...seriously</i>
<i>fall for him...</i>

134
00:08:25,058 --> 00:08:28,529
Curse you, Pegasus, whose
dreams are you hiding in?...

135
00:08:28,562 --> 00:08:33,667
[groan] All this pacing back and
forth is killing my feet...

136
00:08:35,035 --> 00:08:39,973
He keeps popping up everywhere
and yet we're unable to capture
him. It's very annoying.

137
00:08:40,006 --> 00:08:47,413
<i>[distant giggling]</i>

138
00:08:47,480 --> 00:08:50,016
Ah. Hello, girls.

139
00:08:50,050 --> 00:08:52,418
You've finally awakened, I see.

140
00:08:52,485 --> 00:09:03,403
[playful giggling]

141
00:09:09,776 --> 00:09:13,547
I know how you feel, but let's
not smash the orb just yet.

142
00:09:13,547 --> 00:09:16,917
Yes, they're expendable pawns,
but they have their uses.

143
00:09:19,786 --> 00:09:21,354
I know, thank you.

144
00:09:21,387 --> 00:09:26,392
I'm already fully aware that our
queen, Nehalennia, is becoming
quite upset.

145
00:09:29,563 --> 00:09:32,566
Mamo.

146
00:09:32,599 --> 00:09:34,635
“Mamo's ” what they
call you, right?

147
00:09:34,701 --> 00:09:36,637
You again?

148
00:09:36,703 --> 00:09:38,805
So, got a minute?

149
00:09:38,872 --> 00:09:40,106
No, sorry, I'm in
kind of a hurry.

150
00:09:42,643 --> 00:09:43,944
Argh!

151
00:09:45,445 --> 00:09:48,148
[gasp]

152
00:09:55,889 --> 00:09:56,890
[grunt]

153
00:09:56,923 --> 00:09:58,925
[gasp] Come on, why not?

154
00:09:58,925 --> 00:10:00,867
She doesn't have to know.

155
00:10:00,867 --> 00:10:02,869
That's not really
the issue here.

156
00:10:02,903 --> 00:10:05,839
You don't find me attractive?

157
00:10:05,872 --> 00:10:07,574
I didn't say that...

158
00:10:07,608 --> 00:10:09,710
I'm just not interested
in anyone but her.

159
00:10:09,743 --> 00:10:12,679
Why? That doesn't make sense!

160
00:10:12,713 --> 00:10:14,881
<i>What's so special about</i>
<i>a girl like her?</i>

161
00:10:14,915 --> 00:10:17,518
Like I said, I'm in a hurry.

162
00:10:17,551 --> 00:10:19,686
You can't go!

163
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:23,857
You're...the first one I've
ever been serious about.

164
00:10:26,893 --> 00:10:29,129
Why not?

165
00:10:32,633 --> 00:10:38,204
<i>Fine, just tell me: What's so</i>
<i>great about that Usagi? Why</i>
<i>choose her?</i>

166
00:10:38,238 --> 00:10:43,076
She's full of
dreams, that's why.

167
00:10:44,444 --> 00:10:46,913
Dreams?

168
00:10:48,582 --> 00:10:56,590
<i>♪ Sailor Moon</i>

169
00:11:06,272 --> 00:11:09,943
<i>♪ Sailor Moon</i>

170
00:11:12,245 --> 00:11:19,686
Oh. There you are... Madame
Zirconia wants to see us...
She seems pretty upset.

171
00:11:21,321 --> 00:11:22,488
[sigh]

172
00:11:22,523 --> 00:11:25,358
What's up with that guy? Did you
already take care of him?

173
00:11:25,358 --> 00:11:26,960
No.

174
00:11:26,993 --> 00:11:29,696
Ah, that might explain it.

175
00:11:29,763 --> 00:11:34,835
Is having dreams...such
an amazing thing?

176
00:11:34,868 --> 00:11:36,870
Huh?

177
00:11:36,870 --> 00:11:41,041
Look around, there are so many
pleasures right in front of
us...

178
00:11:41,041 --> 00:11:45,779
Why would anyone prefer dreams,
when you don't even know if
they'll come true?

179
00:11:48,014 --> 00:11:50,016
Meaning..?

180
00:11:50,050 --> 00:11:51,785
One...!
Argh!

181
00:11:51,818 --> 00:11:53,219
Two...!

182
00:11:53,219 --> 00:11:54,955
Three!

183
00:11:54,988 --> 00:11:57,157
[agonizing screams]

184
00:11:57,190 --> 00:11:58,859
Huh?

185
00:11:58,892 --> 00:12:00,326
What're you doing??

186
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:02,402
Just as I thought,
no Dream Mirror.

187
00:12:02,402 --> 00:12:04,404
Huh?

188
00:12:04,404 --> 00:12:07,908
Why is it that we don't dream
beautiful dreams, like other
people do?

189
00:12:07,908 --> 00:12:13,847
Huh??...Well, be glad we don't.
Having dreams just makes life
difficult.

190
00:12:13,880 --> 00:12:16,249
[gasp]

191
00:12:19,019 --> 00:12:23,857
<i>Huh? Hey! Where are you going?</i>
<i>Get me off of this thing!</i>

192
00:12:25,425 --> 00:12:26,927
(Zirconia)
You are not worthy!

193
00:12:26,993 --> 00:12:33,233
Nevertheless, Queen Nehalennia
deigns to have words with you.
So listen well.

194
00:12:33,266 --> 00:12:34,434
Queen who?

195
00:12:34,601 --> 00:12:36,369
...Ne‐who‐what‐ia?

196
00:12:36,402 --> 00:12:39,439
Forgive me, madame, but
who is Queen Nehalennia?

197
00:12:39,506 --> 00:12:43,276
She's the great, all‐powerful
ruler of our people...

198
00:12:43,343 --> 00:12:47,280
as well as the most beautiful
being in this universe.

199
00:12:47,347 --> 00:12:49,182
[gasps]

200
00:12:49,215 --> 00:12:54,087
We are ready, your majesty!
Appear and speak to us!

201
00:13:00,226 --> 00:13:02,402
[gasps]

202
00:13:03,303 --> 00:13:06,106
I despise waiting.

203
00:13:06,139 --> 00:13:09,976
And I have no use for
useless servants...

204
00:13:09,976 --> 00:13:17,618
Fail once more and the magic
spell cast upon you will be gone
by the next new moon....

205
00:13:17,651 --> 00:13:24,424
Hurry& You must hurry.

206
00:13:31,097 --> 00:13:36,236
I think she made herself clear.
There can be no more failures.

207
00:13:36,269 --> 00:13:38,404
Just a minute.

208
00:13:38,438 --> 00:13:39,806
Hm?

209
00:13:39,840 --> 00:13:43,243
What did she mean by that stuff
about a magic spell cast upon
us?

210
00:13:45,145 --> 00:13:49,916
[evil laughter]

211
00:13:49,950 --> 00:13:52,452
Excuse me, but what's so funny?

212
00:13:52,485 --> 00:13:56,923
Oh, dear, dear. So you still
haven't realized what you really
are?

213
00:13:56,957 --> 00:13:58,424
[gasp]

214
00:13:58,458 --> 00:14:00,961
Time you learned...

215
00:14:00,994 --> 00:14:05,205
All right, then. See yourselves
as you truly are!

216
00:14:06,206 --> 00:14:08,208
[gasps]

217
00:14:11,545 --> 00:14:13,614
It can't be!!

218
00:14:13,647 --> 00:14:17,150
Wait‐‐ Are you saying...?

219
00:14:17,183 --> 00:14:19,285
... tha what we really are??

220
00:14:19,319 --> 00:14:21,387
Now do you understand?

221
00:14:21,454 --> 00:14:23,223
You are not human...

222
00:14:23,289 --> 00:14:26,960
<i>I merely used magic to</i>
<i>give you a human form.</i>

223
00:14:28,061 --> 00:14:32,633
I see. And that's why we don't
have beautiful dreams?

224
00:14:32,666 --> 00:14:34,134
Huh?

225
00:14:34,167 --> 00:14:39,072
This magic, it will last only
till the coming of the next
new moon...

226
00:14:39,139 --> 00:14:41,575
<i>...But there is one hope.</i>

227
00:14:41,642 --> 00:14:46,479
Pegasus. Find him and capture
him, because only by using the

228
00:14:46,513 --> 00:14:49,716
power of that horn on his head
known as the Golden Crystal

229
00:14:49,750 --> 00:14:52,185
...will you be able
to remain as you are!

230
00:14:52,318 --> 00:14:55,255
<i>There is no other way!</i>

231
00:15:06,540 --> 00:15:09,175
<i>(Fish's Ey)</i>
<i>Waiting for someon?</i>

232
00:15:09,209 --> 00:15:11,077
Huh? Argh!

233
00:15:13,346 --> 00:15:15,448
Not you again...

234
00:15:15,516 --> 00:15:18,351
[giggle] Are you
meeting that girl?

235
00:15:18,384 --> 00:15:19,520
That's right.

236
00:15:19,553 --> 00:15:24,090
Do you enjoy being
with her, Mamo?

237
00:15:24,124 --> 00:15:26,527
Yeah, of course I do.

238
00:15:26,560 --> 00:15:29,730
Ah.

239
00:15:29,763 --> 00:15:35,969
Tell me... what if there were
bad people who were after you?

240
00:15:36,036 --> 00:15:38,138
Huh?

241
00:15:38,138 --> 00:15:41,608
And what if I promised to
protect you from those people...

242
00:15:41,642 --> 00:15:44,310
...and I really meant it...

243
00:15:44,310 --> 00:15:50,083
And all I asked in return was
that you stay with me until the
next new moon...

244
00:15:50,116 --> 00:15:52,318
would you do it?

245
00:15:56,056 --> 00:15:57,624
What're you talking about?

246
00:15:57,658 --> 00:16:00,226
I'm serious! I promise! I
really, really promise! So‐‐

247
00:16:00,260 --> 00:16:04,671
[sad sigh]

248
00:16:07,107 --> 00:16:09,409
I'm not sure I follow.

249
00:16:09,442 --> 00:16:14,180
But being make‐believe lovers in
return for a favor seems pretty
sad, if you ask me.

250
00:16:14,180 --> 00:16:15,448
[embarrassed gasp]

251
00:16:16,583 --> 00:16:19,252
What kind of dream is that?

252
00:16:31,197 --> 00:16:34,334
I see. Dreams again...

253
00:16:34,367 --> 00:16:36,102
I get it now...

254
00:16:36,136 --> 00:16:38,639
It must be nice
having such fine dreams...

255
00:16:40,206 --> 00:16:42,142
Well, big deal!

256
00:16:43,276 --> 00:16:44,210
[gasp]

257
00:16:44,210 --> 00:16:45,145
One...

258
00:16:45,178 --> 00:16:46,212
Huh!?

259
00:16:46,279 --> 00:16:47,147
Two...!

260
00:16:47,180 --> 00:16:48,515
Argh!

261
00:16:48,549 --> 00:16:49,516
And three.

262
00:16:49,550 --> 00:16:52,318
[agonizing scream]

263
00:16:53,386 --> 00:16:56,823
Chibi‐Usa, why don't you be a
good little girl and run on
home now?

264
00:16:56,857 --> 00:16:58,124
Don't want to!

265
00:16:58,158 --> 00:17:00,694
I have a date, so I'm not
asking, I'm telling y‐‐

266
00:17:00,727 --> 00:17:01,735
[Mamoru's screams]
That voice!

267
00:17:01,802 --> 00:17:05,305
(Mamoru)
[agonizing screams]

268
00:17:05,338 --> 00:17:06,206
It's Mamo!

269
00:17:06,239 --> 00:17:07,708
We have to transform!

270
00:17:07,741 --> 00:17:15,348
<i>(Chibi‐Usa / Usagi)</i>
<i>Moon Crisis Make Up!</i>

271
00:17:16,517 --> 00:17:26,560
<i>♪ Sailor Moon...</i>
<i>Sailor Moon... ♪</i>

272
00:17:26,560 --> 00:17:45,579
<i>♪ Sailor Moon...</i>
<i>Sailor Moon... ♪</i>

273
00:17:46,580 --> 00:17:51,351
(Fish's Eye)
Ah yes, The Dream Mirror
that shows... your
beautiful dreams...

274
00:17:51,384 --> 00:17:52,252
Huh.

275
00:17:52,285 --> 00:17:53,453
<i>(Sailor Moon)</i>
<i>Hold it right there!</i>

276
00:17:56,890 --> 00:17:59,726
There are many good‐looking
men in this world.

277
00:17:59,760 --> 00:18:03,604
But you've attacked the
best‐looking of them all, which
means you've got good taste.

278
00:18:03,637 --> 00:18:05,639
Way | good for your own good!

279
00:18:05,639 --> 00:18:07,440
We're the Pretty Guardians...

280
00:18:07,473 --> 00:18:09,309
...who fight for
love and justice!!

281
00:18:09,375 --> 00:18:14,881
I am Sailor Moon!

282
00:18:14,915 --> 00:18:18,384
And I am Sailor Chibi Moon!

283
00:18:18,418 --> 00:18:20,621
And in the name of the Moon...

284
00:18:20,654 --> 00:18:22,656
‐we'll punish you!
‐we'll punish you!

285
00:18:22,656 --> 00:18:26,660
So...you two will keep
interfering till the very end.

286
00:18:26,660 --> 00:18:28,562
The end?

287
00:18:28,595 --> 00:18:34,500
Come forth, my Lemures
Tobihaneru, the Trampoline
Acrobat.

288
00:18:34,568 --> 00:18:37,170
Here!

289
00:18:38,839 --> 00:18:40,841
Keep these girls busy
for me, will you?

290
00:18:40,907 --> 00:18:43,644
As you wish!

291
00:18:43,677 --> 00:18:45,411
[gasps]

292
00:18:45,445 --> 00:18:48,682
And now, it's show time!

293
00:18:49,650 --> 00:18:51,484
Huh?

294
00:18:51,518 --> 00:18:52,519
[screams]

295
00:18:52,519 --> 00:18:54,287
Up you go!

296
00:18:54,320 --> 00:18:56,823
[screaming]

297
00:18:56,990 --> 00:18:58,825
Very good!

298
00:18:58,859 --> 00:19:02,335
Now all together! Down we go...

299
00:19:02,368 --> 00:19:05,205
And up we go...!

300
00:19:05,539 --> 00:19:06,707
Fun, eh?

301
00:19:06,773 --> 00:19:07,874
Higher!

302
00:19:07,941 --> 00:19:09,610
That's it!

303
00:19:09,643 --> 00:19:11,311
Feel the burn!

304
00:19:11,344 --> 00:19:12,846
In your thigh muscles!

305
00:19:12,879 --> 00:19:15,716
Now, let's have a
look at your dreams.

306
00:19:17,684 --> 00:19:25,458
[agonizing screams]

307
00:19:28,461 --> 00:19:30,897
[gasp] Pegasus isn't here!

308
00:19:32,999 --> 00:19:37,403
But‐‐ It can't be, I was
sure you were the one..!

309
00:19:38,338 --> 00:19:40,574
No, no, no, no!

310
00:19:49,550 --> 00:19:51,317
[gasp]

311
00:20:07,508 --> 00:20:09,610
[gasps] Mamo!

312
00:20:10,777 --> 00:20:12,312
Chibi Moon!

313
00:20:12,979 --> 00:20:17,684
Please, Pegasus! Protect
everyone's dream!

314
00:20:19,886 --> 00:20:23,356
Twinkle Yell!

315
00:20:35,335 --> 00:20:43,677
♪

316
00:20:43,710 --> 00:20:50,416
Moon Gorgeous Meditation!

317
00:21:02,769 --> 00:21:07,574
Stage out!

318
00:21:17,450 --> 00:21:22,355
(Usagi)
[groaning] Oh, Mamo,
you alright?

319
00:21:22,388 --> 00:21:25,959
[delirious groans]

320
00:21:28,028 --> 00:21:40,774
<i>[rainfall]</i>

321
00:21:40,807 --> 00:21:45,812
That weather report
lied! It's <i>pouring!</i>

322
00:21:47,948 --> 00:21:49,983
[gasp] It's that girl...

323
00:21:53,620 --> 00:21:57,490
<i>(Usag)</i>
<i>What's wrong?</i>

324
00:21:57,490 --> 00:22:01,968
Come on, now. You won't
be much of a love rival
looking like that.

325
00:22:18,619 --> 00:22:27,994
<i>♪</i>

326
00:22:27,994 --> 00:22:48,014
<i>♪</i>

327
00:22:48,014 --> 00:23:08,041
<i>♪</i>

328
00:23:08,041 --> 00:23:28,061
<i>♪</i>

329
00:23:28,061 --> 00:23:47,213
<i>♪</i>

330
00:23:53,119 --> 00:23:55,455
<i>(Fish's Eye)</i>
<i>What's your greatest dream?</i>

331
00:23:55,522 --> 00:23:58,224
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Mine? To marry Mamo,</i>
<i>of course. [giggle]</i>

332
00:23:58,258 --> 00:24:01,635
<i>(Fish's Eye)</i>
<i>I envy you and your</i>
<i>beautiful dreams...</i>

333
00:24:01,635 --> 00:24:05,539
<i>...I wish‐‐ I wish I</i>
<i>had dreams, too...</i>

334
00:24:05,572 --> 00:24:07,140
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>What's the matter?</i>

335
00:24:07,140 --> 00:24:10,544
<i>(Fish's Eye)</i>
<i>I'm sorry! Please die so I can</i>
<i>make my dreams come true!</i>

336
00:24:10,577 --> 00:24:15,916
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Next time on Sailor Moon SuperS:</i>
<i>"Mirrors of Dreams: The Amazon's</i>
<i>Last Stage."...</i>

337
00:24:15,949 --> 00:24:18,218
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>The moonlight is a</i>
<i>messenger of love...</i>

